result.execSummary:
Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

3:35 PM Prosecuting attorney Daniel Joseph Tombasco in court for the State of Wisconsin. Defendant Madison G. Moore in court.  Attorney Donald J Bielski in court for Madison G. Moore. Clerk N. Nobile.
MINUTES: 21CM1453/22CM71/22CM783. Victim rights compliance. Matter is resolved and Attorney Bielski files the plea questionnaire in court. 

Case 22CM783: On State's motion, case is dismissed and read in.

Case 22CM71: Defendant entered a plea of guilty to counts 1-2; found guilty by the court. Court orders withheld sentence; defendant placed on probation for 2 years w/conditions. No contact with Maxwell U except through My Family Wizard and pursuant to the Court Order in Case 22FA52 in regards to the exchange of the CH in a public place. Any violation of probation shall be reported to the Court within 30 days and at least 30 days prior to the termination of the DE's probation. No sentence credit if revoked.

Case 21CM1453: Defendant entered a plea of guilty to count 1; found guilty by the court. On State's motion, count 2 is dismissed and read in. Court orders withheld sentence; defendant placed on probation for 2 years w/conditions. No contact with Maxwell U except through My Family Wizard and pursuant to the Court Order in Case 22FA52 in regards to the exchange of the CH in a public place. Any violation of probation shall be reported to the Court within 30 days and at least 30 days prior to the termination of the DE's probation. No sentence credit if revoked.  

Court costs, DV surcharge and DNA surcharges ordered. Defendant is ordered to submit a DNA sample; written notice provided to defendant in Case 22CM71. DE will be eligible for expunction upon successful completion of probation w/ no violations or criminal activity.
Final pre-trial on September 20, 2022 at 03:30 pm.
